# Strapi CMS Integration

## Architecture

```
src/lib/strapi.ts    → Raw Strapi API client (fetchers + interfaces)
src/lib/content.ts   → Content abstraction layer (Strapi-first, JSON fallback)
src/lib/media.ts     → Strapi media URL helper
src/lib/types.ts     → Shared TypeScript interfaces
```

## Adding New Content Types

1. Create schema in `reloadux-cms/src/api/{name}/content-types/{name}/schema.json`
2. Create routes/controllers/services files (Strapi v5 requires all three)
3. Add Strapi interface and fetcher in `src/lib/strapi.ts`
4. Add content function in `src/lib/content.ts` with try/catch fallback
5. Add TypeScript types in `src/lib/types.ts`

## API Token

- Stored in `.env.local` as `STRAPI_API_TOKEN`
- Admin JWT tokens do NOT work with Strapi v5 Content API — only API tokens
- Strapi runs at `http://localhost:1337`
- Admin: `salihashahzad23@gmail.com` / `Admin1234!`

## Seed Script

`reloadux-cms/seed.js` populates all content types. Uses the API token (not admin JWT) for Content API calls. Run with `node seed.js` from the CMS directory.
